I"<p>Hello and welcome to the first ever episode of the BITEsize Paediatrics podcast!</p>

<p>Do you know what it takes to become a specialist in paediatric dentistry (UK)? If not, this episode should help you out!</p>

<p>Join Yasmin and Saif as they interview Dr. Carly Dixon - a speciality registrar in paediatric dentistry and assessment lead at the University of Manchester Dental School.</p>

<p>In this episode we cover topics such as:</p>

<p>- Why choose paediatric dentistry in the first place?!<br />
- Building your portfolio during dental school and postgraduate training.<br />
- The career path taken to become a paediatric specialist and consultant.<br />
- Paediatric dentistry exams.<br />
- Masters degrees vs. training posts.<br />
- Academic Clinical Fellowship and Lectureship programmes.</p>

<p>Extra resources to accompany this episode can be found on our <a href="https://www.instagram.com/mpdssoc/?hl=en">social media</a> and <a href="https://linktr.ee/Mpdssoc">linktree</a> @MPDSSOC.</p>

<p>Happy listening!</p>
